holographic_plus
================

A hybrid long-term memory provider for Hermes Agent: it extends the holographic
(HRR) fact store with dense semantic embeddings and LLM-based fact extraction,
and merges all signals in a single hybrid retrieval pass.

This project builds on prior work, gratefully credited:

- The base holographic memory provider (the `MemoryProvider` integration, the
  HRR (Holographic Reduced Representations) retrieval, the SQLite fact store,
  trust scoring, and entity resolution) was created by **dusterbloom** for
  NousResearch/hermes-agent (PR #2351) and is licensed MIT. holographic_plus
  subclasses it; all credit for the holographic foundation is theirs.

- Holographic Reduced Representations, the vector-symbolic technique underlying
  the holographic retrieval, are due to **Tony A. Plate**, "Holographic Reduced
  Representations," IEEE Transactions on Neural Networks, 6(3):623-641, 1995.

The original contributions of this project are the dense embedding retrieval
layer (`embeddings.py`, `embed_store.py`), the LLM-based fact extraction and
its persistent queue (`llm_extract.py`, `extract_queue.py`), the optimized
retriever (`retrieval_plus.py`), and the hybrid scoring that merges dense
similarity with the holographic signals.

